This is hands down my go to lasagna recipe. I usually omit the spinach (picky son) and use 3 boxes of Pomi marinara sauce, 1 lb of mild sausage, 1 lb of low fat ground beef, no carrots or brown sugar, a cup of dry red wine, and De Cecco lasagna pasta that you can use right out of the box to layer into the recipe to save time. Also, instead of the standard sized baking dish, I've used 2 square 8x8" disposable aluminum baking pans with lids to keep on for my family of 2 and either give the other one away to some deserving person or to pop into the freezer. I've also made this recipe as written and it's very good, with the exception of being short on the sauce but with cooking the pasta ahead of layering, you don't need as much sauce.

Rating: 4
I have been making this lasagna for years! As reviewers have suggested, leave out the brown sugar... if you use the excellent San Marzano tomatoes from Costco you won't miss it! Even if you don't have access to that tomato, add more carrots to sweeten the sauce (AND make it healthier). I also add add more garlic, a glass of dry red wine (can't hurt), and throw in a piece of Parmigiano-Reggiano rind I keep in the freezer... the longer you let the sauce simmer the better it is! I quadruple the sauce just to have in the freezer... Enjoy!!

