Very tasty recipe! I would give it 3.5 forks if I could, but then again, it may not be fair to rate the recipe since I did modify somewhat. Like others, I made 1 1/2 times the sauce and left out the brown sugar. I did not use that much fresh basil, as it seemed like a lot to me. Instead, I supplemented with Italian seasoning blend and some extra dried thyme. I used 2 links of Italian sausage and 6 oz of lean ground beef. I also left out the spinach. I think I let the sauce cook a bit too long, so I used about a cup of the pasta water to correct, and this seemed like a good consistency. I layered the pasta and cheese my own way, as I like several thinner layers. I used nearly all the sauce and cheese, which entirely filled a 13x9 pan. Baked for 40 minutes covered, then 25 uncovered, let rest for 10 and it was delicious, everyone went for seconds :)

