For the first time ever I took a risk and used a recipe I had never tried before for a dinner party. Just as many others have mentioned it was a HUGE hit! I read through the suggestions before making it, and here are the changes I made (which definitely worked): 1. DOUBLE THE SAUCE! 2. Use 1 lb of each meat ingredient 3. Use sweet sausage and spicy sausage 4. When doubling the sauce, do not double the brown sugar 5. Add fresh mushrooms to sauce 6. Add extra spinach to ricotta mixture (I used whole ricotta, not skim) 7. Make sure to use a deep dish, I used 13 X 9 deep dish and broke up extra noodles to extend the length of the lasagna 8. Make sure to drain water from the ricotta and the spinach 9. Use extra cheese, mozzarella slices work great 10. Do not follow the amounts suggested for sauce when layering the lasagna, always use extra so the sauce is thick. **use no-boil lasanga noodles to cut back time! Thank you everyone for the great suggestions! This took me a couple hours from start to finish, so I suggest making it ahead and storing it in the fridge until about 1 1/2 hours before you wish to serve it.

