to Saskatoon..... the suace portion of recipe...says "Cover and simmer until flavors blend and sauce measures about 5 cups." This is not just the liquid or only the liquid, this means the whole deal, meat and all .....no wonder why you couldnt taste anything else. Carrotts, though round are easy to chop. First, take and cut in half across as to shorten the carrott, then careful take a small slice as to be able to lay the carrott down on a flat edge, then slice down into four or five wafers, turn on their side and chop away. Give this lasagna another try and dont add 5 cups of tomatoe sauce. Good Luck and happy holidays!

Rating: 4
This is absolutely the BEST lasagna! To the cook from Saskatoon - I believe your problem was with the ingredients. First, "28 oz. crushed tomatoes with added puree" - that's the description you look for on the can. The recipe isn't vague, really. The right can will say "Crushed tomatoes with added puree". That's what you want. And ground pepperoni - WAY different from spicy sausage. Regarding the crushed dried red pepper - if you look in your baking aisle in the spices, you'll see what the recipe calls for: dried red pepper. Is that what you used? You can certainly tweek the amounts of everything. But please do give it another try with the right ingredients -I made this last weekend and my guests declared that it's the only lasagna they will ever want. Good luck!

