The perfect comfort food! Definitely double the sauce. I split the recipe into two 8 x 8 pans. I cooked one right away. For the other one, I lined the baking pan with Press'n Seal wrap, assembled the lasagna and placed the pan in the freezer. Once the dish was frozen solid, I pulled it out of the pan and sealed it up. When I'm ready to cook it, I'll just peel out of the wrap and place it back in the pan. This way I can still use my pan rather than letting it sit unused in a deep freeze. Even better, I have a great meal, ready in just the time it takes to bake. Yum!

