Rating: 4
this is a great recipe - def double the sauce. a trick i use since i also only have a 9 by 13 pan: wrap the whole bottom of the pan in tin foil, with lots of extra up around the sides. then build it up using the tin foil as extra wall, fold it over the top, and when you are ready to brown the top just cut down the middle of the foil with sheers. by then the lasagna is cooked enough that the layers stay together by themsleves, and anything that leaks does so down inside between the foil and the pan. works for me!

