After being totally overwhelmed by the reviews, I tackled this one (with the help of the Lord!)and this is what I did. I increased some of the ingredients as per the other cooks; 1 1/2 c onion, 1 cup carrots, 3 TB garlic, 8 ounces ground turkey(instead of beef), 3 Jenny o sweet turkey sausage (and added some red pepper flakes at the end of cooking to control the spiciness), 2 cans of 28 oz Contadina crushed tomatoes with roasted garlic,(Tomatoe paste stayed same except I added 1/2 C water) 1/2 cup fresh basil, 1 1/2 TB oregano, 2 bay leaves. Since Mozzarella comes in 1 lb package, I left it at 1 lb.(Instead of putting it on the top , I used extra parmesan) I couldn't imagine not adding that extra tomatoes as I had just the right amount of sauce for one pan. I also added a little garlic powder to the cheese mixture. Next time I'll try sundried tomatoes for an extra kick.

