Rating: 3
If you're going to go to the trouble of making lasagna, I would definitely recommend this recipe. It took up the better part of my day to throw together, but it was worth it-- the house smells so good while it's baking. I took the others' advice and doubled the sauce, including the meat; lasagna would have been far too dry if made as written. And since I'm not the biggest ricotta fan, I used only one tub, which seemed like enough. I added two cloves of garlic to the ricotta/spinach mixture to up what I find to be flavorless cheese. Lastly, I baked this in a 10x15 inch pan. If you double the sauce, there's probably no way to fit everything in a significantly smaller dish. Don't be too impatient to dig in once out of the oven; the resting period seemed crucial to getting the lasagna to firm up nicely.

