Rating: 3
This was great basic lasagna recipe. I, too, doubled the sauce. Whenever I make any kind of red sauce I make a ton so I can freeze some for later. It was great over homemade cheese tortellini's later that week. Back to the recipe. I made 2 slight changes. I blended shredded/chopped fresh basil in with the ricotta cheese and I used no boil noodles. Since I used the no boil noodles I increased the amount of sauce I used by at least 2 cups. This avoided the dried out texture you can get when you use that type of noodle. I also agree with a previous post- It best to let the lasagna rest for at least 15 minutes. It is much easier to cut that way and you don't have it sliding all over the place!

