Rating: 3
This is my (and my family's) favorite lasagna recipe. But I do agree with a couple of points other reviewers have made. I have a few suggestions that make this the "perfect lasagna recipe." First of all, double the amount of sauce - this takes care of the "dryness" problem some other reviewers mentioned. Second of all, don't use the "no-boil" lasagna noodles. They absorb too much of the sauce. It's worth it to use the old fashioned boil-first noodles. The recipe does say to "season with salt & pepper." Don't forget this step - it makes a big difference. Finally, use whole milk ricotta. It's worth it!

